2.2 Quick Start
===============

This walkthrough takes you from a raw recording to a rendered clip in
five steps.

  1. *Transcribe a recording*

          M-x eve-transcribe RET

     Select the directory containing your ‘.mp4’ files.  Eve starts ‘eve
     transcribe’ in the background.  When it finishes, the manifest
     opens automatically in eve-mode.

  2. *Read through the transcript*

     Navigate with ‘j’ / ‘k’.  The buffer shows each spoken segment as a
     block of text.  Timestamps appear in the right margin.

  3. *Delete unwanted content*

     Place point on a word and press ‘d’ to delete it.  Press ‘D’ to
     delete the whole segment.  Press ‘f’ on a word to tag it as a
     filler; press ‘F’ to delete all tagged fillers at once.

  4. *Compile a draft preview*

          C-c C-c

     Eve validates the manifest, pre-renders changed segments in the
     background, and produces a draft ‘.mp4’ in seconds.  Play it back
     with ‘C-u C-c SPC’ or your usual player.

  5. *Export for delivery*

          C-u C-c C-c

     Compiles at full H.264 quality using the same segment cache.  Only
     segments that haven't been cached yet need re-encoding.


