File: eve.info,  Node: Concept (1),  Next: Editing b-roll metadata,  Up: B-Roll

7.1 Concept
===========

B-roll is supplementary footage that plays over (or instead of) the main
recording.  Eve supports two b-roll modes:

   • *Replace* — the b-roll clip completely replaces the source video
     for the duration of the segment.  The source audio is preserved (or
     you can use the b-roll's audio).

   • *Pip* (picture-in-picture) — the b-roll is composited as an overlay
     on top of the source video.  Position and size are configurable.


File: eve.info,  Node: Editing b-roll metadata,  Next: Placeholders and templates,  Prev: Concept (1),  Up: B-Roll

7.2 Editing b-roll metadata
===========================

Key         Command                         Description
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
‘b’         ‘eve-edit-broll’                Edit the b-roll entry for the current segment.
‘B’         ‘eve-toggle-broll-continue’     Mark the segment as continuing the previous b-roll chain.
‘C-c C-b’   ‘eve-edit-broll-placeholders’   Edit the placeholder substitutions for the segment.

   B-roll metadata is stored inside the segment's ‘edit.broll’ field in
the JSON.


File: eve.info,  Node: Placeholders and templates,  Next: Continuation chains,  Prev: Editing b-roll metadata,  Up: B-Roll

7.3 Placeholders and templates
==============================

B-roll entries can contain placeholder tokens (e.g., ‘[PRODUCT]’) that
are resolved at render time.  Use ‘C-c C-b’ to define the concrete
values for each placeholder in the current segment.


File: eve.info,  Node: Continuation chains,  Next: Audio policy,  Prev: Placeholders and templates,  Up: B-Roll

7.4 Continuation chains
=======================

When a b-roll clip spans multiple consecutive segments, mark the second
and subsequent segments with ‘B’ (‘eve-toggle-broll-continue’).  The
renderer treats the chain as a single b-roll clip that plays through all
of them, advancing its offset continuously rather than restarting.


File: eve.info,  Node: Audio policy,  Prev: Continuation chains,  Up: B-Roll

7.5 Audio policy
================

Each b-roll entry has an ‘audio’ field:

   • ‘source’ (default) — use the audio from the main recording.
   • ‘broll’ — use the audio track from the b-roll clip.

   Edit this via ‘M-x eve-edit-broll’ on the relevant segment.


